09/10/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The second, bilateral phase of the EU screening to harmonise Croatian legislation with that of the EU under the Regional Policy chapter of the acquis was completed in Brussels on Friday (October 6th). 
During the two-day talks, Croatia's negotiators briefed the European Commission (EC) on steps Zagreb has taken to bring domestic laws and institutions in line with relevant EU standards.
Speaking on the eve of Croatia's Independence Day, October 8th, President Stipe Mesic said the chief task confronting politicians is the completion of EU membership talks and the adoption of EU standards. 
(Vjesnik - 07/10/06; HRT - 06/10/06)
